		<legis-type>A BILL</legis-type>
		<official-title>To amend the Federal Election Campaign Act of 1971 to
		  prohibit the conversion of leadership PAC funds to personal
		  use.</official-title>
	</form>
	<legis-body id="H6814BA90E1D44C71B7D77EFB13ED2631" style="OLC">
		<section id="HC2737C54469F49548721EDE2D27C5DD8" section-type="section-one">
      <enum>1.</enum>
      <header>Short Title</header>
      <text display-inline="no-display-inline">This Act may be cited as the
			 <quote>
          <short-title>Leadership PAC Limitation
			 Act</short-title>
        </quote>.</text>
		</section>
    <section id="H64ACF9F13ADB40F1801270B83F6CFE6E">
      <enum>2.</enum>
      <header>Prohibiting
			 Conversion of Leadership PAC Funds to Personal Use</header>
			<subsection id="H32F31801B36F4F2DA0A323D9A3438640">
        <enum>(a)</enum>
        <header>Prohibition</header>
        <text display-inline="yes-display-inline">
          <cato:entity xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="law-citation">
            <cato:entity-ref entity-type="act" value="Federal Election Campaign Act of 1971/s:313/ss:b/p:1">Section 313(b)(1) of the Federal Election
			 Campaign Act of 1971</cato:entity-ref> (<cato:entity-ref entity-type="uscode" value="usc/2/439a/b/1">2 U.S.C. 439a(b)(1)</cato:entity-ref>)</cato:entity> is amended by inserting after
			 <quote>subsection (a)</quote> the following: <quote>or funds of a leadership
			 PAC (as defined in <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="act" value="Federal Election Campaign Act of 1971/s:304/ss:i/p:8/sp:B">section 304(i)(8)(B)</cato:entity-ref>)</quote>.</text>
			</subsection>
      <subsection id="HF7F0D20D4BD5492BA795D865B021FA87">
        <enum>(b)</enum>
        <header>Effective
			 Date</header>
        <text>The amendment made by <cato:entity-ref xmlns:cato="http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml" entity-type="act" value="Leadership PAC Limitation Act/s:2/ss:a" proposed="true">subsection (a)</cato:entity-ref> shall apply with
			 respect to elections occurring on or after the date of the enactment of this
			 Act.</text>
			</subsection>
    </section>
